data.title: The Development of The Nitrous Oxide-Acetylene Flame For Aas
data.meta_description:
The development of the nitrous oxide-acetylene flame for aas - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides a personal account of the development of the nitrous oxide-acetylene flame for atomic absorption spectroscopy by J.B. Willis. 

[1] Willis began working with atomic absorption spectroscopy in 1958 and experimented with various flame types, initially using air-coal gas and air-acetylene flames. He developed new burner and nebulizer designs to improve the technique.
